Today was my companies employee appreciation lunch. We have 200 employees here at HQ and the company usually caters from Sale and Pepe. Seeing that there are more employees keeping Kosher and Halal, the CEO asked me to order food to accommodate those employees. I decided to order from Bravo and if I tell you how embarrassed I was doesn't even begin to describe it. The cost of $16 per person (we ordered for 10 as the minimum) should have covered a decent sized sandwich, and the sides (pickles, cole slaw etc). The sandwiches looked like they were thrown on a platter with no care, almost every sandwiches bread was torn, and to make matter worse, there was only, what I can describe as, less than 1 ounce of meat per sandwich. Imagine seeing this pitiful thing sitting next to a non-kosher version that was 3-4 times the size and looked and smelled 1000 times better.  Since the few kosher people were so turned off, and stuck with the salad and fruit that was provided,  there was a lot of food left over, I took the time to look at every sandwich and this is what I found, Roast beef - on average 2 (yes 2) slices of meat (just because you ball it up doesn't make it any better), Pastrami - 4-6 slices, Salami - 4!, Turkey was the only 1/2 way decent amount of meat at 1st glance, but when you open the bread you noticed it took up half the room. I wish I could post the photos I took so everyone can see what was delivered. I should have ordered from Mr. Broadway, at least they take pride in their food.
